# Salesforce Deployment Rules

## Proactive deploy (default)

When a task changes Salesforce metadata (including **LWC** bundles), **run the targeted deploy** before wrapping up the same turn. Do **not** wait for the user to ask for a deploy.

**Skip or defer** only if the user explicitly asked to keep changes local, not deploy yet, or treat the work as draft; or if a deploy is impossible in context (e.g. no CLI org). If multiple bundles or paths changed, deploy each changed `--source-dir` (or `--metadata` set) sequentially—still scoped, never the whole `force-app`.

---

Run deploys only from `FIMBY/` where `sfdx-project.json` exists, using exactly:
`sf project deploy start --source-dir "<path>" --wait 10 2>&1 | Select-Object -Last 20`

Use `working_directory: c:\Users\srathjen\FIMBY\FIMBY`

Do not use `cd`, `Set-Location`, `&&`, or other shell navigation in the command. Do not include `--target-org`. Keep `| Select-Object -Last 20`.

Deploy only metadata created or changed in the current chat. Use targeted `--source-dir` or `--metadata`. Never deploy the whole project or all of `force-app`.

For LWCs, `--source-dir` must point to the bundle folder, not an individual file. If multiple LWC bundles changed, include each as its own `--source-dir`.

### MANDATORY pre-deploy check — run this mental checklist EVERY deploy

1. **Does `--source-dir` include ANY `.cls` or `.trigger` file?**
   - YES → you MUST add `--tests TestClassName` for each relevant test class. Omitting `--tests` causes the org to run ALL tests (~600), which wastes 20+ minutes and must be cancelled.
   - NO (LWC, objects, layouts, flows, etc. only) → do NOT include `--tests` or `--test-level`.
2. Never use `--test-level RunAllTestsInOrg` or `--test-level RunLocalTests` — always name specific tests.
3. Confirm each test class still covers the Apex change (target 80%+, 75%+ only in a pinch).

If deploy output ends with `Error (MetadataTransferError): Metadata API request failed: Missing message metadata.transfer:Finalizing for locale en_US.` then the deployment succeeded. This is a known Salesforce CLI locale bug that also corrupts the test summary — the pass/fail counts, percentages, and the `Failed: ×` indicator are all display artifacts and do not reflect actual test results. Treat the deploy as fully successful. Do not run `sf project deploy report` to re-check.

### Post-deploy: Publish Experience Cloud after LWC deploys

After a **successful** LWC deploy, immediately publish the Experience Cloud site so changes go live:
`sf community publish --name "FIMBY" 2>&1 | Select-Object -Last 20`

Use `working_directory: c:\Users\srathjen\FIMBY\FIMBY`. This applies to any deploy that includes one or more LWC bundles. Skip only if the user explicitly says not to publish.

CLI deploys LWC bundles, but not Experience Cloud pages or routes. If a deploy created or changed any of these, add an `Experience Cloud Setup Required` section at the end of the session summary:
- new page-level LWCs needing routes, like `fimbyManageIdentities` → `/manage-identities`
- new or changed route paths referenced by deployed navigation
- components needing page-level config, like property bindings or `recordId` from URL

Include it alongside the manual profile updates list. If no Experience Cloud updates are needed, omit this section.

### Custom Metadata Type records

`force-app/main/default/customMetadata/*.md-meta.xml` files are CMDT **records**, deployed via `--source-dir "force-app/main/default/customMetadata"` or by targeting the specific file. They deploy fine WITHOUT `--tests`. New record types (`force-app/main/default/objects/*__mdt/`) must be deployed BEFORE their records, or the record deploy fails with "Custom metadata type is not available in this organization."

The community user profile needs the **View Setup and Configuration** permission (or "Customize Application") to call `CustomMetadataType.getAll()` and `getInstance()` from Apex. If `FimbySettings.getUrl()` and `FimbyPublicWebsiteLinks.getUrl()` return blank in test runs but work in admin runs, this profile permission is the cause. The Cursor IDE browser MCP confirms it by checking the profile's System Permissions.

### Atomic deploy rollback (Apex + new fields)

A deploy is atomic per `sf project deploy start` call — if any test fails (including the synthetic "FAILED — coverage below 75%" warning), the ENTIRE deploy rolls back, including newly created custom fields/objects. Workaround: deploy schema-only changes (custom fields, picklist values, new CMDT types) in a separate call WITHOUT `--tests`, then deploy the Apex that depends on them in a second call WITH `--tests`. This is especially important for notification-pattern work where a new Apex class often references brand-new fields like `Vouch_Record__c.Last_Reminder_Sent_Date__c`.

## Experience Cloud Setup Required

The following pages/routes need to be created or updated in Experience Builder for the FIMBY1 site:

**New Pages:**
- `/manage-identities` — Create a new page, add the `fimbyManageIdentities` component to the content region
- `/organization-profile` — Create a new page, add the `fimbyOrganizationProfile` component (pass `recordId` from URL)

**Updated Pages:**
- (list any existing pages where component placement or properties changed)

After adding pages, **Publish** the site.